Absolutely awful station. Not cleaned at all. The most disappointing station I've ever visited in the world.

Usually unmanned. You access the platforms via stairs. There is a bike ramp but I don't believe there is wheelchair access. Very dingy and I doubt that lone travelers would want to use the station when it is dark. It is however very handy if you want to avoid travelling all the way to bought station.
This is even worse than a lot of the stations from near where I am from up north! Pokesdown station is tired and depressing, I'd avoid the station at all costs, use Christchurch or Bournmouth.
